maxCardinality.name: maxCardinality
maxCardinality.description: The maximum number of instances a CharacteristicValue can take on. For example, zero to five phone numbers in a group calling plan, where five is the value for the maxCardinality.

isUnique.name: isUnique
isUnique.description: Specifies if the value of this characteristic is unique across all entities instantiated from the specification that uses this characteristc. For example, consider a ProductSpecification for a set-top box, with a CharacteristicSpecification cardID. Each set-top box must have a different value for cardID, so this isUnique attribute would be set to true for the characteristic.

The values of the attributes in the CharacteristicValueSpecification object describe the values of the attributes that a corresponding Characteristic object can take on.

Lists the possible severities that can be allocated to an Alarm. The values are consistent with ITU-T Recommendation X.733.
Once an alarm has been cleared, its perceived severity is set to 'cleared' and can no longer be set.

alarmRaisedTime.description: Indicates the time (as a date + time) at which the alarm occurred at its source.

alarmChangedTime.description: Indicates the last date and time when the alarm is changed on the alarm-owning system. Any change to the alarm whether coming from the alarmed resource, or triggered by a change from the client is changing this time.

  was detected by the NE, while the alarmReportingTime would be the time this alarm was stored in the alarm list of the EMS.

maxCardinality.name: maxCardinality

isUnique.name: isUnique
isUnique.description: Specifies if the value of this characteristic is unique across all entities instantiated from the specification that uses this characteristc. For example, consider a ProductSpecification for a set-top box, with a CharacteristicSpecification cardID. Each set-top box must have a different value for cardID, so this isUnique attribute would be set to true for the characteristic.

resourceSpecCharacteristic.name: resourceSpecCharacteristic
resourceSpecCharacteristic.description: A characteristic quality or distinctive feature of a ResourceSpecification.  The characteristic can be take on a discrete value, such as color, can take on a range of values, (for example, sensitivity of 100-240 mV), or can be derived from a formula (for example, usage time (hrs) = 30 - talk time *3). Certain characteristics, such as color, may be configured during the ordering or some other process.

maximumQuantity.name: maximumQuantity

minimumQuantity.name: minimumQuantity
minimumQuantity.description: The minimum number of the related resource that should be instantiated, for example a rack must have at least 1 card

characteristic.name: characteristic
characteristic.description: A characteristic that refines the relationship. For example, consider the relationship between a slot and a card. ruleViolation.description: A list of rules that were violated in this test measure

conformanceComparatorLower.name: conformanceComparatorLower
conformanceComparatorLower.description:
An operator that when applied on a value specifies whether a 
threshold is crossed or ceased to be crossed. This operator is used to compare with the conformanceTargetLower if used.

conformanceComparatorExact.name: conformanceComparatorExact
conformanceComparatorExact.description:
An operator that when applied on a value specifies whether it 
is the same target value or not. This operator is used to compare with the conformanceTargetExact if used.

conformanceComparatorUpper.name: conformanceComparatorUpper
conformanceComparatorUpper.description:
An operator that when applied on a value specifies whether a 
threshold is crossed or ceased to be crossed. This operator is used to compare with the conformanceTargetUpper if used.

conformanceTargetLower.name: conformanceTargetLower
conformanceTargetLower.description:
A value used to determine if the threshold is crossed or ceases 
to be crossed. It represents the lower limit. The value should be less than the conformanceTargetUpper if used. The conformance comparators should also be logically defined so as to not lead to a logically impossible condition.

conformanceTargetUpper.name: conformanceTargetUpper
conformanceTargetUpper.description:
A value used to determine if the threshold is crossed or ceases 
to be crossed. It represents the Upper limit. The value should be greater than the conformanceTargetLower if used. The conformance comparators should also be logically defined so as to not lead to a logically impossible condition.

description.name: description
description.description: Description for the MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule .

numberOfAllowedCrossing.name: numberOfAllowedCrossing
numberOfAllowedCrossing.description:
The number of allowed crossing occurrences in reference to the 
tolerancePeriod without a consequence being initiated.

thresholdRuleSeverity.name: thresholdRuleSeverity
thresholdRuleSeverity.description:
A threshold can be generated in different severity levels. A 
crossing for each level may require a different condition and possibly trigger a different consequence.

conformanceTargetExact.name: conformanceTargetExact
conformanceTargetExact.description: To cater for values that are not numerical test metrics (e.g. a DSL line can be Synchronised or Unsynchronised. If the latter, the test should result in a rule violation).The allowed value can contain a REGEX expression.

tolerancePeriod.name: tolerancePeriod
tolerancePeriod.description: A time interval in a given unit of time

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Time interval (number of seconds, minutes, hours, etc.)

units.name: units
units.description: Unit of time (seconds, minutes, hours, etc.)

appliedConsequence.name: appliedConsequence
appliedConsequence.description: An Applied Consequence defines the action (prescribed action or notification) to take when a MeasureThresholdRuleViolation occurs.

appliedAction.name: appliedAction
appliedAction.description:
The action for a violated threshold. This could be a hyperlink to 
the action.

description.name: description
description.description: A narrative that explains in detail what the consequence is.

name.name: name
name.description:
A word, term, or phrase by which Consequence is known and 
distinguished from other MetricDefMeasureConsequences.

repeatAction.name: repeatAction
repeatAction.description:
An indicator used to specify that a consequence should cease 
being applied if a value is in the same range as the previous value or continue being applied if a value is in the same range as the previous value.  
If the repeatAction is True, if the consequence is always applied as soon as the MetricMeasure value is in the range of values and if the repeatAction is False, the consequence is applied only if the previous MetricMeasure value was not in the same range.

unitOfMeasure.name: unitOfMeasure
unitOfMeasure.description: The unit of measure for the metric values, such as meters, cubic yards, kilograms [ISO 1000].

value.name: value
value.description: Reference to Characteristic

testMeasureCharacteristic.description: A list of additional characteristics that characterize this test measurement (usageCharacteristic [*])

testSpecification.description: Product Test specification reference: ProductTestSpecification(s) required to realize a Test Specification.

incidentRef.name: incidentRef
incidentRef.description: An Incident is a record of an event that has altered the operational state of a entity (Resource, Service or Customers Product).

conformanceComparatorLower.name: conformanceComparatorLower
conformanceComparatorLower.description:
An operator that when applied on a value specifies whether a 
threshold is crossed or ceased to be crossed. This operator is used to Service Test Management API REST Specification compare with the conformanceTargetLower if used.

conformanceComparatorUpper.name: conformanceComparatorUpper
conformanceComparatorUpper.description:
An operator that when applied on a value specifies whether a 
threshold is crossed or ceased to be crossed. This operator is used to compare with the conformanceTargetUpper if used.

conformanceComparatorExact.name: conformanceComparatorExact
conformanceComparatorExact.description:
An operator that when applied on a value specifies whether the 
value is the same or not. This operator is used to compare with the conformanceTargetExact if used.

conformanceTargetExact.name: conformanceTargetExact
conformanceTargetExact.description: To cater for values that are not numerical test metrics (e.g. a DSL line can be Synchronised or Unsynchronised. If the latter, the test should result in a rule violation). The allowed value can contain a REGEX expression.

conformanceTargetLower.name: conformanceTargetLower
conformanceTargetLower.description:
A value used to determine if the threshold is crossed or ceases 
to be crossed. It represents the lower limit. The value should be less than the conformanceTargetUpper if used. The conformance comparators should also be logically defined so as to not lead to a logically impossible condition.

conformanceTargetUpper.name: conformanceTargetUpper
conformanceTargetUpper.description:
A value used to determine if the threshold is crossed or ceases 
to be crossed. It represents the Upper limit. The value should be greater than the conformanceTargetLower if used. The conformance comparators should also be logically defined so as to not lead to a logically impossible condition.

consequence.name: consequence
consequence.description: A list of consequences (actions, notifications) that will arise if the threshold is crossed

description.name: description
description.description: A narrative that explains in detail what the consequence is.

name.name: name
name.description:
A word, term, or phrase by which a 
MetricDefMeasureConsequence is known and distinguished from other MetricDefMeasureConsequences.

prescribeAction.name: prescribeAction
prescribeAction.description:
Recommended remedy for a violated threshold. This could be 
the hyperlink to the action.

repeatAction.name: repeatAction
repeatAction.description:
An indicator used to specify that a consequence should cease 
being applied if a value is in the same range as the previous value or continue being applied if a value is in the same range as the previous value. 
If the repeatAction is True, if the consequence is always applied as soon as the MetricMeasure value is in the range of values and if the repeatAction is False, the consequence is applied only if the previous MetricMeasure value was not in the same range.

description.name: description
description.description: Description for the MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule .

numberOfAllowedCrossing.name: numberOfAllowedCrossing
numberOfAllowedCrossing.description:
The number of allowed crossing occurrences in reference to the 
tolerancePeriod without a consequence being initiated.

thresholdRuleSeverity.name: thresholdRuleSeverity
thresholdRuleSeverity.description:
A threshold can be generated in different severity levels. A 
crossing for each level may require a different condition and possibly trigger a different consequence.

cycleSpecification.name: cycleSpecification
cycleSpecification.description: The polymorphic attributes @type, @schemaLocation & @referredType are related to the BillingCycleSpecification entity and not the BillingCycleSpecificationRefOrValue class itself

billingDateShift.name: billingDateShift
billingDateShift.description: An offset of a billing/settlement date. The offset is expressed as number of days with regard to the start of the billing/settlement period.

billingPeriod.name: billingPeriod
billingPeriod.description: A billing time period. It can be recurring, for example: week, month, quarter of year, year .

chargeDateOffset.name: chargeDateOffset
chargeDateOffset.description: An offset of a date through which charges previously received by the billing system will appear on the bill. The offset is expressed as number of days with regard to the start of the BillingPeriod.

creditDateOffset.name: creditDateOffset
creditDateOffset.description: An offset of a date through which credits previously received by the billing system will appear on the bill. The offset is expressed as number of days with regard to the start of the BillingPeriod.

description.name: description
description.description: An explanation regarding this billing cycle specification

frequency.name: frequency
frequency.description: Frequency of the billing cycle (monthly for instance)

mailingDateOffset.name: mailingDateOffset
mailingDateOffset.description: An offset of a customer bill mailing date. The offset is expressed as number of days with regard to the start of the BillingPeriod.

paymentDueDateOffset.name: paymentDueDateOffset
paymentDueDateOffset.description: An offset of a payment due date. The offset is expressed as number of days with regard to the start of the BillingPeriod.

oneOf.name: cycleSpecification_variant_1
oneOf.description: BillingCycleSpecification reference. A description of when to initiate a billing cycle and the various sub steps of a billing cycle.

paymentPlan.name: paymentPlan
paymentPlan.description: A list of payment plans that are active or expired for the account, for example if the customer had difficulty in paying

id.name: id
id.description: Identifier of the plan within list of the plans (for entities with list)

numberOfPayments.name: numberOfPayments
numberOfPayments.description: Number of payments used to spread the global payment

paymentFrequency.name: paymentFrequency
paymentFrequency.description: Frequency of the payments, such as monthly and bimonthly

priority.name: priority
priority.description: Priority of the payment plan

status.name: status
status.description: Status of the payment plan (effective, ineffective)

paymentMethod.name: paymentMethod
paymentMethod.description: PaymentMethod reference. A payment method defines a specific mean of payment (e.g direct debit).

financialAccount.name: financialAccount
financialAccount.description: AccountReceivable reference. An account of money owed by a party to another entity in exchange for goods or services that have been delivered or used. An account receivable aggregates the amounts of one or more party accounts (billing or settlement) owned by a given party.

ratingType.name: ratingType
ratingType.description: Indicates whether the account follows a specific payment option such as prepaid or postpaid

name.name: name
name.description: A human-readable name for the agreement

agreementType.name: agreementType
agreementType.description: The type of the agreement. For example commercial

id.name: id
id.description: Identifier of the Agreement item (generally it is a sequence number 01, 02, 03, ...)

description.name: description
description.description: Text that explains the term or condition of the agreement.

validFor.name: validFor
validFor.description: A period of time, either as a deadline (endDateTime only) a startDateTime only, or both

startDateTime.name: startDateTime
startDateTime.description: Start of the time period, using IETC-RFC-3339 format

endDateTime.name: endDateTime
endDateTime.description: End of the time period, using IETC-RFC-3339 format

role.name: role
role.description: Role played by the related party or party role in the context of the specific entity it is linked to. Such as 'initiator', 'customer',  'salesAgent', 'user'

partyId.name: partyId
partyId.description: The identifier of the engaged party that is linked to the PartyRole object.

partyName.name: partyName
partyName.description: The name of the engaged party that is linked to the PartyRole object.

description.name: description
description.description: Narrative that explains the agreement and details about the it , such as why the agreement is taking place.

relatedDocument.name: relatedDocument
relatedDocument.description: Documents related to the agreement, suc as signed off contract

items.name: items
items.description: The polymorphic attributes @type, @schemaLocation & @referredType are related to the Attachment entity and not the AttachmentRefOrValue class itself

description.name: description
description.description: A narrative text describing the content of the attachment

url.name: url
url.description: Uniform Resource Locator, is a web page address (a subset of URI)

content.name: content
content.description: The actual contents of the attachment object, if embedded, encoded as base64

size.name: size
size.description: An amount in a given unit

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Numeric value in a given unit

attachmentType.name: attachmentType
attachmentType.description: a business characterization of the purpose of the attachment, for example logo, instructionManual, contractCopy

mimeType.name: mimeType
mimeType.description: a technical characterization of the attachment content format using IETF Mime Types

description.name: description
description.description: A narrative text describing the content of the attachment

url.name: url
url.description: Link to the attachment media/content

valueType.name: valueType
valueType.description: Data type of the value of the characteristic

relationshipType.name: relationshipType
relationshipType.description: The type of relationship

creationDate.name: creationDate
creationDate.description: The date and time the document was created. A date and time formatted in compliance with the ISO8601 standard must be used.

description.name: description
description.description: free-text description of the document

name.name: name
name.description: a String. Name of the DocumentSpecification

version.name: version
version.description: A string, a version of the DocumentSpecification.

lastUpdate.name: lastUpdate
lastUpdate.description: The date and time the document was last modified. A date and time formatted in compliance with the ISO8601 standard must be used.

lifecycleState.name: lifecycleState
lifecycleState.description: The life cycle state of the document.

version.name: version
version.description: A particular form or variety of an artefact that is different from others or from the original. The form represents differences in properties that characterize an artefact, that are not enough to warrant creating a new artefact

name.name: name
name.description: A string used to give a name to the document

initialDate.name: initialDate
initialDate.description: Date at which the agreement was initialized

statementOfIntent.name: statementOfIntent
statementOfIntent.description: An overview and goals of the Agreement

status.name: status
status.description: The current status of the agreement. Typical values are: in process, approved and rejected

version.name: version
version.description: A string identifying the version of the agreement

description.name: description
description.description: A narrative that explains in detail what the agreement specification is about.

date.name: date
date.description: The date associated with the authorization state.

signatureRepresentation.name: signatureRepresentation
signatureRepresentation.description: Indication that represents whether the signature is a physical paper signature or a digital signature.

state.name: state
state.description: Current status of the authorization, for example in process, approved, rejected.

id.name: id
id.description: Unique identifier of the related agreement

relationshipType.name: relationshipType
relationshipType.description: Type of relationship such as containment, substitution, dependency, exclusivity

partyPrivacyProfile.name: partyPrivacyProfile
partyPrivacyProfile.description: The privacy profiles that are the subject of the agreement

items.name: items
items.description: Reference to Party Privacy Profile resource

partyPrivacyProfileCharacteristic.name: partyPrivacyProfileCharacteristic
partyPrivacyProfileCharacteristic.description: A list of (typically) high criticality characteristics whose chosen privacy rules are included in the agreement

relatedParty.name: relatedParty
relatedParty.description: A list of parties to which the allowed use of the characteristic applies.

privacyUsagePurpose.name: privacyUsagePurpose
privacyUsagePurpose.description: Defines the purpose authorized or refused for the characteristic (e.g. ADMIN, INFORMATION, MARKETING, RESEARCH, etc.

lastUpdate.name: lastUpdate

lifecycleStatus.name: lifecycleStatus

relatedParty.name: relatedParty
relatedParty.description: List of parties or party roles involved in the definition or management of the specification

role.name: role
role.description: Role played by the related party or party role in the context of the specific entity it is linked to. Such as 'initiator', 'customer',  'salesAgent', 'user'

partyId.name: partyId
partyId.description: The identifier of the engaged party that is linked to the PartyRole object.

partyName.name: partyName

validFor.name: validFor

endDateTime.name: endDateTime

version.name: version
version.description: The version of the specification, in case it is desired to maintain multiple versions of profile specifications

specCharacteristic.name: specCharacteristic
specCharacteristic.description: List of characteristics of the specification, whose values would typically be supplied when the profile is instantiated

description.name: description
description.description: Description of the characteristic

criticalityLevel.name: criticalityLevel
criticalityLevel.description: Level of criticality for this characteristic of personal identifiable information (e.g. in terms of the damage if this item was breached), such as low, medium, high.

privacyUsagePurpose.description: Defines the purpose authorized or refused for the characteristic (e.g. ADMIN, INFORMATION, MARKETING, RESEARCH).

allowedRole.name: allowedRole
allowedRole.description: A list of roles in the organization who are allowed access to this characteristic

@baseType.name: @baseType
@baseType.description: When sub-classing, this defines the super-class

@schemaLocation.name: @schemaLocation
@schemaLocation.description: A URI to a JSON-Schema file that defines additional attributes and relationships

state.name: state
state.description: Current state of the operation task

items.name: items
items.description: An alarm defined by reference or value. The polymorphic attributes @type, @schemaLocation & @referredType are related to the Alarm entity and not the AlarmRefOrValue class itself

externalAlarmId.name: externalAlarmId
externalAlarmId.description: An identifier of the alarm in the source system.

state.name: state
state.description: Defines the alarm state during its life cycle (raised, updated, cleared).

alarmType.name: alarmType
alarmType.description: Categorizes the alarm (X.733 8.1.1, 3GPP TS 32.111-2 Annex A)

perceivedSeverity.name: perceivedSeverity
perceivedSeverity.description:
Lists the possible severities that can be allocated to an Alarm. The values are consistent with ITU-T Recommendation X.733.
Once an alarm has been cleared, its perceived severity is set to 'cleared' and can no longer be set.

probableCause.name: probableCause
probableCause.description: Provides the probable cause of the alarm. The values are consistent with ITU-T Recommendation X.733 or 3GPP TS 32.111-2 Annex B.

specificProblem.name: specificProblem
specificProblem.description: Provides more specific information about the alarm.

alarmedObjectType.name: alarmedObjectType
alarmedObjectType.description: The type (class) of the managed object associated with the event.

alarmedObject.name: alarmedObject
alarmedObject.description: Reference to object which affected by Alarm (AlarmedObject).

alarmDetails.name: alarmDetails
alarmDetails.description: Contains further information on the alarm.

alarmRaisedTime.name: alarmRaisedTime
alarmRaisedTime.description: Indicates the time (as a date + time) at which the alarm occurred at its source.

alarmChangedTime.name: alarmChangedTime
alarmChangedTime.description: Indicates the last date and time when the alarm is changed on the alarm-owning system. Any change to the alarm whether coming from the alarmed resource, or triggered by a change from the client is changing this time.

alarmClearedTime.name: alarmClearedTime
alarmClearedTime.description: Indicates the time (as a date + time) at which the alarm is cleared at the source.

alarmReportingTime.name: alarmReportingTime
alarmReportingTime.description:
Indicates the time (as a date + time) at which the alarm was reported by the owning OSS. It might be different from the alarmRaisedTime. For instance, if the alarm list is maintained by an EMS, the alarmRaisedtime would be the time the alarm
  was detected by the NE, while the alarmReportingTime would be the time this alarm was stored in the alarm list of the EMS.

ackState.name: ackState
ackState.description: Provides the Acknowledgement State of the alarm (unacknowledged, acknowledged).

ackSystemId.name: ackSystemId
ackSystemId.description: Provides the name of the system that last changed the ackState of an alarm, i.e. acknowledged or unacknowledged the alarm.

ackUserId.name: ackUserId
ackUserId.description: Provides the id of the user who has last changed the ack state of the alarm, i.e. acknowledged or unacknowledged the alarm.

items.name: items
items.description: Service reference, for when Service is used by other entities.

alarmEscalation.name: alarmEscalation
alarmEscalation.description: Indicates if this alarm has been escalated or not.

clearSystemId.name: clearSystemId
clearSystemId.description: Provides the id of the system where the user who invoked the alarmCleared operation is located.

clearUserId.name: clearUserId
clearUserId.description: Provides the id of the user who invoked the alarmCleared operation

comment.name: comment
comment.description: Provides list of Comments regards Alarm.

userId.name: userId
userId.description: Indicates the user commenting the alarm.

systemId.name: systemId
systemId.description: Indicates the system identifier on which the client set the comment.

time.name: time
time.description: Indicates the time commenting the alarm

comment.name: comment
comment.description: Indicates the text of the comment.

crossedThresholdInformation.name: crossedThresholdInformation
crossedThresholdInformation.description: Identifies the details of the threshold that has been crossed.

direction.name: direction
direction.description: Indicates the threshold crossing direction: up or down.

granularity.name: granularity
granularity.description: Indicates the granularity at which the indicator is evaluated for threshold crossing

indicatorName.name: indicatorName
indicatorName.description: Indicates the name of indicator which crossed the threshold.

indicatorUnit.name: indicatorUnit
indicatorUnit.description: Indicates the unit of the measurement of the indicator corresponding to the threshold that has been crossed.

observedValue.name: observedValue
observedValue.description: Indicates the value of the indicator which crossed the threshold.

thresholdCrossingDescription.name: thresholdCrossingDescription
thresholdCrossingDescription.description: Indicates further information on the threshold crossing alarm.

isRootCause.name: isRootCause
isRootCause.description: Indicates whether the alarm is a root cause alarm..

plannedOutageIndicator.name: plannedOutageIndicator
plannedOutageIndicator.description: Indicates that the Managed Object (related to this alarm) is in planned outage (in planned maintenance, or out-of-service).

proposedRepairedActions.name: proposedRepairedActions
proposedRepairedActions.description: Indicates proposed repair actions, if known to the system emitting the alarm.

serviceAffecting.name: serviceAffecting
serviceAffecting.description: Indicates whether the alarm affects service or not.

place.name: place
place.description: List of related places, which are affected by Alarm.

externalIdentifier.name: externalIdentifier
externalIdentifier.description: Collection of external identifiers

owner.name: owner
owner.description: Name of the external system that owns the entity.

externalIdentifierType.name: externalIdentifierType
externalIdentifierType.description: Type of the identification, typically would be the type of the entity within the external system

id.name: id
id.description: identification of the entity within the external system.

alarmPattern.name: alarmPattern
alarmPattern.description: Alarm patterns to match target alarms. An alarm will match if all of the attributes in any of the patterns compare equal to those attributes of the alarm.
